    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-08-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1269"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1269">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/2070.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">E. C. Bryan</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Am fully conversant situation Parral, Mexico, also Santa Barbara. Leaders of
                    occupying forces Manuel Chao and Monclova Herrera made demand August 10 for
                    10,000 pesos, not on Long and Parral and Durango Railroad alone, all foreign
                    interests were included, and paid 6,500 pesos immediately, balance unpaid. Last
                    advices, 14th, Chao also demanded all mining interests keep operating under
                    threat turn men loose in mines and take ores. Also if money not paid would not
                    be responsible for acts of men in his forces, meaning looting and destroying
                    property. Pleased to deliver any special instructions American Consular Agent
                    Parral also American residents and Chao.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. C. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
